which is a tablet-based interface.

00:05:20.170 --> 00:05:22.100
Any of you who have ever
seen a flame artist work,

00:05:22.100 --> 00:05:26.430
they use a tablet and they're constantly
going like this on the tablet and you're

00:05:26.430 --> 00:05:28.050
wondering what in the world they're
doing and stuff's happening on screen.

00:05:28.110 --> 00:05:29.220
We support gestures.

00:05:29.320 --> 00:05:31.100
It's using the ink technology.

00:05:31.100 --> 00:05:34.960
It lets you work in a full screen mode
where you can actually have the canvas

00:05:34.960 --> 00:05:38.660
filling your screen and you're not
actually required to have all your tools

00:05:38.670 --> 00:05:40.100
visible if you don't want to see them
and you're working with a client live.

00:05:40.100 --> 00:05:41.950
It's really great technology.

00:05:42.100 --> 00:05:45.100
And of course we have
the keyframe editor.

00:05:45.160 --> 00:05:48.380
Filter effects, of course,
are important to any graphics

00:05:48.460 --> 00:05:50.100
application these days.

00:05:50.130 --> 00:05:54.220
We use hardware accelerated,
actually GPU accelerated filters are

00:05:54.220 --> 00:05:58.100
very important to motion and they allow
you to see things like Gaussian blurs,

00:05:58.100 --> 00:06:02.310
light rays in real time,
which is pretty much unprecedented

00:06:02.310 --> 00:06:04.100
at 30 Hz in the past.

00:06:04.440 --> 00:06:08.010
Light rays support for
After Effects plug-ins as well.

00:06:08.100 --> 00:06:11.090
Particles is an integral part of motion.

00:06:11.090 --> 00:06:14.460
They're actually built into the
motion engine so they're integrated

00:06:14.460 --> 00:06:16.090
with the whole application.

00:06:16.130 --> 00:06:17.100
They're not just an add-on.

00:06:17.100 --> 00:06:21.440
What that means is it's a
sprite-based implementation so you

00:06:21.440 --> 00:06:26.100
actually have things like movies,
graphics files, text,

00:06:26.100 --> 00:06:28.100
anything can be turned into a particle.

00:06:28.130 --> 00:06:30.100
It's actually a really dynamic system.

00:06:30.100 --> 00:06:35.140
We also include presets for smoke
and sparkles and things like that.

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:38.780
Unlimited layering, and of course in any
graphics application,

00:06:38.870 --> 00:06:42.590
anyone who's ever opened a Photoshop file
lately from their graphics house

00:06:42.630 --> 00:06:46.300
has seen 99 layers of things
layered over the top of one another.

00:06:46.400 --> 00:06:47.690
